.SS "string SlimeMarkUp\&.Core\&.IncludeTagHandler\&.Parse (string line)"

.PP
Parses the specified line to extract an include directive and returns the contents of the referenced file, wrapped with comment markers\&. If the specified file does not exist or cannot be read, the returned string contains an HTML comment describing the error\&. The method does not throw exceptions for missing or unreadable files; instead, it returns an error message in the output\&.

.PP
\fBParameters\fP
.RS 4
\fIline\fP The line of text to parse for an include directive\&. Must contain a valid include pattern; otherwise, the method returns null\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
A string containing the contents of the included file, wrapped with start and end comment markers\&. Returns null if the line does not contain a valid include directive\&. Returns an error comment if the file is not found or cannot be read\&.
.RE
